## Overview

Extend the engine's `roll()` method to handle Fate dice and exploding dice, and update output formatting to display explosion chains and Fate ladders. This chunk also includes comprehensive tests.

**Depends on:** Chunks 3-1 (parser extensions) and 3-2 (systems module)

## Type Reference (from Story 1)

DO NOT redefine - these already exist in `src/types.rs`:

```rust
pub struct DiceExpression {
    count: u32,
    sides: DiceSides,
    modifiers: Vec<Modifier>,
    exploding: bool,
}

pub enum DiceSides {
    Standard(u32),
    Fate,
}

pub struct RollResult {
    expression: DiceExpression,
    rolls: Vec<i32>,
    kept: Vec<i32>,
    dropped: Vec<i32>,
    modifier_total: i32,
    total: i32,
    explosions: Vec<ExplosionChain>,
    fate_ladder: Option<String>,
}

pub struct ExplosionChain {
    values: Vec<i32>,
    total: i32,
}
```

## Implementation

### Part 1: Engine Extensions (`src/engine.rs`)

Extend the `roll()` method in `DiceEngine` to handle Fate and exploding dice:

```rust
pub fn roll(&mut self, expr: &DiceExpression) -> Result<RollResult, DiceError> {
    let mut rolls = Vec::new();
    let mut explosions = Vec::new();

    match &expr.sides {
        DiceSides::Standard(sides) => {
            for _ in 0..expr.count {
                let chain = crate::systems::roll_standard(&mut self.rng, *sides, expr.exploding);
                rolls.push(chain.total);
                if expr.exploding && chain.values.len() > 1 {
                    explosions.push(chain);
                }
            }
        }
        DiceSides::Fate => {
            for _ in 0..expr.count {
                rolls.push(crate::systems::roll_fate(&mut self.rng));
            }
        }
    }

    // Apply keep/drop modifiers (from Story 1)
    let (kept, dropped) = self.apply_keep_drop(&rolls, &expr.modifiers);

    // Calculate modifier total
    let modifier_total = self.sum_modifiers(&expr.modifiers);

    // Calculate final total
    let total = kept.iter().sum::<i32>() + modifier_total;

    // Fate ladder if applicable
    let fate_ladder = match expr.sides {
        DiceSides::Fate => Some(crate::systems::fate_ladder(total).to_string()),
        _ => None,
    };

    Ok(RollResult {
        expression: expr.clone(),
        rolls,
        kept,
        dropped,
        modifier_total,
        total,
        explosions,
        fate_ladder,
    })
}
```

Behavior:
- For standard dice: calls `systems::roll_standard()` for each die
  - Tracks explosion chains separately if `exploding: true` and chain has > 1 value
  - The roll total (already summed in chain) gets added to `rolls` vec
- For Fate dice: calls `systems::roll_fate()` for each die
- Applies existing keep/drop logic to final rolls
- Calculates Fate ladder name if sides are Fate
- Returns complete RollResult with all fields populated

### Part 2: Output Extensions (`src/output.rs`)

Add three helper functions and update `format_roll()` to use them:

```rust
/// Format an explosion chain: "[6! → 6! → 4] = 16"
fn format_explosion(chain: &ExplosionChain) -> String {
    if chain.values.len() == 1 {
        // No explosion happened
        format!("[{}]", chain.values[0])
    } else {
        // Format as "[v1! → v2! → v3] = total"
        let chain_str = chain.values
            .iter()
            .enumerate()
            .map(|(i, v)| {
                let suffix = if i < chain.values.len() - 1 { "!" } else { "" };
                format!("{}{}", v, suffix)
            })
            .collect::<Vec<_>>()
            .join(" → ");
        format!("[{}] = {}", chain_str, chain.total)
    }
}

/// Format Fate dice rolls: "[+] [-] [ ] [+]"
fn format_fate_dice(rolls: &[i32]) -> String {
    rolls.iter()
        .map(|v| match v {
            -1 => "[-]",
            0 => "[ ]",
            1 => "[+]",
            _ => "[?]",
        })
        .collect::<Vec<_>>()
        .join(" ")
}

/// Format Fate total with ladder: "+3 (Good)"
fn format_fate_total(total: i32, ladder: &str) -> String {
    if total >= 0 {
        format!("+{} ({})", total, ladder)
    } else {
        format!("{} ({})", total, ladder)
    }
}
```

Update `format_roll()` to incorporate these:
- When `result.fate_ladder.is_some()`, use `format_fate_dice()` to display individual rolls and `format_fate_total()` for the final total
- When `!result.explosions.is_empty()`, include explosion chain descriptions in output (e.g., "4d6! → [6! → 4] = 10, [3] = 3, [5] = 5")
- Maintain all existing formatting for normal dice

## Tests

### Engine Tests (`tests/engine_test.rs` additions)

```rust
const TEST_SEED: u64 = 0x1A2B3C4D5E6F7890;

#[test]
fn test_fate_dice_result() {
    let expr = parse("4dF").unwrap();
    let mut engine = DiceEngine::with_seed(TEST_SEED);

    let result = engine.roll(&expr).unwrap();
    assert_eq!(result.rolls.len(), 4);
    assert!(result.fate_ladder.is_some());
    for roll in &result.rolls {
        assert!(*roll >= -1 && *roll <= 1);
    }
}

#[test]
fn test_exploding_populates_chains() {
    let expr = parse("d6!").unwrap();
    let mut engine = DiceEngine::with_seed(TEST_SEED);

    // Roll many times to likely get an explosion
    for _ in 0..100 {
        let result = engine.roll(&expr).unwrap();
        if !result.explosions.is_empty() {
            let chain = &result.explosions[0];
            assert!(chain.values.len() > 1);
            assert_eq!(chain.total, chain.values.iter().sum());
            break;
        }
    }
}

#[test]
fn test_fate_with_modifier() {
    let expr = parse("4dF+2").unwrap();
    let mut engine = DiceEngine::with_seed(TEST_SEED);

    let result = engine.roll(&expr).unwrap();
    assert_eq!(result.modifier_total, 2);
    assert!(result.fate_ladder.is_some());
    assert_eq!(result.total, result.rolls.iter().sum::<i32>() + 2);
}
```

### Systems Tests (`tests/systems_test.rs` - new file)

```rust
use sage_dice::systems::{roll_standard, roll_fate, fate_ladder};
use rand::SeedableRng;
use rand::rngs::StdRng;

const TEST_SEED: u64 = 0x1A2B3C4D5E6F7890;

#[test]
fn test_explosion_caps_at_10() {
    let mut rng = StdRng::seed_from_u64(TEST_SEED);
    // Create a mocked scenario or multiple rolls to verify cap
    let chain = roll_standard(&mut rng, 6, true);
    assert!(chain.values.len() <= 11); // Initial roll + max 10 explosions
}

#[test]
fn test_non_exploding_single_value() {
    let mut rng = StdRng::seed_from_u64(TEST_SEED);
    let chain = roll_standard(&mut rng, 6, false);
    assert_eq!(chain.values.len(), 1);
    assert_eq!(chain.total, chain.values[0]);
}

#[test]
fn test_fate_roll_range() {
    let mut rng = StdRng::seed_from_u64(TEST_SEED);
    for _ in 0..100 {
        let v = roll_fate(&mut rng);
        assert!(v >= -1 && v <= 1);
    }
}

#[test]
fn test_fate_ladder_mapping() {
    assert_eq!(fate_ladder(-3), "Terrible");
    assert_eq!(fate_ladder(-2), "Terrible");
    assert_eq!(fate_ladder(-1), "Poor");
    assert_eq!(fate_ladder(0), "Mediocre");
    assert_eq!(fate_ladder(1), "Average");
    assert_eq!(fate_ladder(2), "Fair");
    assert_eq!(fate_ladder(3), "Good");
    assert_eq!(fate_ladder(4), "Great");
    assert_eq!(fate_ladder(5), "Superb");
    assert_eq!(fate_ladder(6), "Fantastic");
    assert_eq!(fate_ladder(7), "Epic");
    assert_eq!(fate_ladder(8), "Legendary");
    assert_eq!(fate_ladder(100), "Legendary");
}

#[test]
fn test_explosion_chain_total() {
    let mut rng = StdRng::seed_from_u64(TEST_SEED);
    let chain = roll_standard(&mut rng, 20, true);
    // Verify total equals sum of values
    assert_eq!(chain.total, chain.values.iter().sum());
}
```

## Success Criteria

- Engine `roll()` method handles both `DiceSides::Fate` and `DiceSides::Standard`
- Exploding dice populate `result.explosions` with chains
- Fate dice populate `result.fate_ladder` with ladder name
- Output formatting displays explosion chains as "[v1! → v2! → v3] = total"
- Output formatting displays Fate dice as "[+] [-] [ ] [+]"
- Output formatting shows Fate ladder: "+3 (Good)"
- Explosion cap enforced at 10 (MAX_EXPLOSIONS)
- All new engine tests pass
- All new systems tests pass
- All Story 1 tests still pass
- `cargo test` passes completely

